race.comment: KIARNI PHOENIX (2) is a sprinter who thrives over these shorter races. Was in the money last time (30.67) over 525m at this track in a Grade 5 but is better suited by this sharper distance. Strike rate this course and distance strong having won three of five tries. Can go on with it. THAT'S OKAY (3) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Reel 'Em Remi (17.56) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Winning chance. KICKER MINI (5) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at The Gardens over 400m behind Zipping Bubbles (23.77) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Shapes as one to consider. TIGER LIKE (4) was strongly fancied last time on the back of a win two back but could only manage second (17.60) at this track. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome.
